<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col">
      <h1 class="mb-4">About Pokemon Rails Explorer</h1>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">

          <h2>Project Overview</h2>

          <p>
            Pokemon Rails Explorer is a Ruby on Rails applicationn that allows users to browse Pokemon, view more detailed information, and rear user reviews generated with Faker.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">

          <h2>Data Sources</h2>

          <ul>
            <li class="mb-3">
              <strong>PokeAPI</strong> – Pokemon names, stats, types, abilities, and moves.
              <p class="mb-0 mt-1">
                The primary data source provides Pokemon data in JSON format through a REST API.
                It includes Pokemon names, Pokedex numbers, physical attributes, abilities,
                moves, and types. The data is imported into the application using the Rails
                seed script.
              </p>
            </li>

            <li class="mb-3">
              <strong>pokemon.json</strong> – Pokemon sprite images.
              <p class="mb-0 mt-1">
                This GitHub repository provides Pokemon sprite images. Since both data sources
                use the Pokedex number as a unique identifier, the sprite images can be matched
                to the Pokemon imported from PokeAPI.
              </p>
            </li>

            <li>
              <strong>Faker</strong> – Random usernames, ratings, and review comments.
              <p class="mb-0 mt-1">
                Faker is used to generate realistic usernames and reviews, providing sample
                data to demonstrate one-to-many relationships and populate the application.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">

          <h2>Database ERD</h2>

          <p>
            This Entity Relationship Diagram shows the database
            structure and relationships used throughout the application.
          </p>

          <%= image_tag "erd.png",
              class: "img-fluid rounded border d-block mx-auto",
              style: "max-width: 800px",
              alt: "Pokemon Rails Explorer ERD" %>

        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">

          <h2>Technologies Used</h2>

          <ul>
            <li>Ruby on Rails</li>
            <li>Bootstrap</li>
            <li>SQLite</li>
            <li>Active Record</li>
            <li>Importmap</li>
          </ul>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>